  "prompt": "What does it mean when someone stares at you?",
  "response": "When someone stares at you, it could mean different things depending on the context:\n\n1. Positive reasons:\n- They find you attractive\n- They're interested in you\n- They're curious about something about you\n- They are lost in thought\n\n2. Neutral reasons:\n- They're people-watching\n- They're daydreaming\n- They're thinking about something else\n- They're unconsciously looking in your direction\n\n3. Potentially negative reasons:\n- They want to intimidate you\n- They're angry or upset with you\n- They're judging you\n- They're trying to make you uncomfortable\n\n4. Other possible reasons:\n- They recognize you from somewhere\n- They're trying to understand or read you\n- They have a social or cultural difference in eye contact norms\n\nThe interpretation depends on the specific situation, body language, and context. If you feel uncomfortable, it's okay to look back, look away, or address the person directly if you feel safe doing so.",
